– 2 –
10 quarterly and annual reports relating to cybersecurity and the progress of the
11 Office; and (5) maintaining certain cybersecurity incident response plans filed by a
12 political subdivision. (NRS 480.924-480.935)
13 Existing law creates the Office of the Chief Information Officer within the
14 Office of the Governor, consisting of certain units, offices and other units, groups,
15 divisions or departments, including the Office of Information Security. (NRS
16 242.080) Sections 2, 3, 5-16, 26 and 27 of this bill move the Nevada Office of
17 Cyber Defense Coordination to the Office of the Chief Information Officer. Section
18 17 of this bill merges the Nevada Office of Cyber Defense Coordination and the
19 Office of Information Security and renames the offices the Office of Information
20 Security and Cyber Defense. Sections 20-22, 28 and 29 of this bill make
21 conforming changes by applying various provisions of existing law relating to the
22 Office of Information Security to the Office of Information Security and Cyber
23 Defense.
24 Existing law requires the Chief Information Officer to appoint a Deputy Chief
25 of the Office of Information Security who is in the classified service of this State.
26 (NRS 242.101) Section 18 renames the position of Deputy Chief of the Office of
27 Information Security the Deputy Director of the Office of Information Security and
28 Cyber Defense and places the Deputy Director of the Office in the unclassified
29 service of this State. Section 31 of this bill provides that the person who is in the
30 position of Deputy Chief of the Office of Information Security on July 1, 2025, is in
31 the classified service and must remain in the classified service until he or she
32 vacates that position.
33 Existing law requires the Chief Information Officer to adopt regulations
34 necessary for the administration of laws relating to information services for state
35 agencies, elected state officers and, under certain circumstances, agencies not under
36 the control of the Governor and local governmental agencies. (NRS 242.111)
37 Section 19 of this bill requires the Chief Information Officer to adopt by regulation
38 the policies and procedures necessary to coordinate the cybersecurity activities of
39 state agencies and local governments.
40 Existing law provides that certain plans and records of a state agency or local
41 government relating to a threat or attack on the security of an information system is
42 not a public record. (NRS 480.935, 480.940) Sections 1, 15 and 16 of this bill
43 similarly provide that such plans and records are not public records and may be
44 disclosed only by the Deputy Director only under certain circumstances.
45 Section 35 of this bill repeals the provisions of law creating and providing for
46 the powers and duties of the Nevada Office of Cyber Defense Coordination within
47 the Department of Public Safety. Sections 23-25 of this bill make conforming
48 changes to revise references to provisions that are repealed by section 35.
