15 2. The continued development of technologies relating to
16 information systems and the expanding and diverse applications of
17 those technologies pose significant implications for the
18 functioning of any infrastructure in this State that is critical to the
19 health, safety and welfare of the people of this State, particularly
20 in the areas of transportation, health care, energy, education, law
21 enforcement and commercial enterprises.
22 3. Information systems and the application of information
23 systems relating to the operation of the State Government and
24 local governments make up a statewide cyberinfrastructure that is
