26 State and the essential functions of government that ensure the
27 protection of the health, safety and welfare of the people of this
28 State.
29 4. Protecting and securing the statewide cyberinfrastructure
30 requires the identification of the areas in which information
31 systems may be vulnerable to attack, unauthorized use or misuse
32 or other dangerous, harmful or destructive acts.
33 5. Protecting and securing the statewide cyberinfrastructure
34 requires an ability to identify and eliminate threats to information
35 systems in both the public and private sectors.
36 6. Protecting and securing the statewide cyberinfrastructure
37 requires a strategic statewide plan for responding to incidents in
38 which information systems are compromised, breached or
